The governing All Progressives Congress (APC), has again expressed its total rejection of the nation’s electoral umpire’s decision on the outcome of the Supreme Court Judgement on Bayelsa state governorship, assuring that the party will seek all the legal means to recover its mandate. LEADERSHIP reports that the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) today issued the certificate of return to the candidate of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) as the validly elected governor of the state. Reacting to the decision of INEC to respect the Supreme Court decision, APC National Chairman, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole said he has written to the commission that the Supreme Court did not say that it should sworn in the PDP’s candidate, Douye Diri. He specifically chided the electoral umpire for assuming the role of court in interpreting tge verdict of the Supreme Court wrongly. According to Oshiomhole, “INEC has decided to assume that the case of Bayelsa is the same with that of Zamfara. INEC has assumed judicial power. “I wrote to INEC after the deliberation with the NWC that if it was the intention of Supreme Court to void the votes of APC “We have consulted and resolve to reject in entirety the decision to issue certificate to the PDP candidate. “We want to put the people of Nigeria on notice and of cause the people of Bayelsa that nobody hide under the judicial cover to impose minority on the people, even INEC is in content of the court.”